##Continuous time model fit
#This is the function that calculates the sum of squares given some parameter values
LVcomp <- function (t, n, parms, fixed){
  ra <- fixed[1]; rc <- fixed[2]
  Ka <- fixed[3]; Kc <- fixed[4]
  with(as.list(parms), {
    dnadt <- ra * n[1] * (Ka - n[1] - a12 * n[2])/Ka
    dncdt <- rc * n[2] * (Kc - n[2] - a21 * n[1])/Kc 
    list(c(dnadt, dncdt))
  })
}
library(deSolve)
parms <- c(0, 0) 
initialN <- c(1, 1)
fixed <- c(ra=0.7816, rc=0.6283, Ka=559.6860, Kc=202.4931)

lsquares.fit<-function(par,data){
  parms <- c(a12 = par[1], a21 = par[2])
  out <- ode(y = initialN, times = 1:20, func = LVcomp, parms=parms, fixed=fixed)
  pa.out <- out[,2]
  pc.out <- out[,3]
  return(sum((pa.out-data[,1])^2)+sum((pc.out-data[,2]))^2)
}
fit1 <- optim(par = parms, fn = lsquares.fit, data = pac1)
fit2 <- optim(par = parms, fn = lsquares.fit, data = pac2)
fit3 <- optim(par = parms, fn = lsquares.fit, data = pac3)
a12 <-mean(c(fit1$par[1],fit2$par[1],fit3$par[1]))
a21 <-mean(c(fit1$par[2],fit2$par[2],fit3$par[2]))
out <- ode(y = initialN, times = 1:20, func = LVcomp, parms=c(a12=a12,a21=a21), fixed=fixed)

##Finding roots and stability

#the rates of change
dn1 <- expression(r1 * n1 * (K1 - n1 - a12 * n2)/K1)
dn2 <- expression(r2 * n2 * (K2 - n2 - a21 * n1)/K2)

#The interior equilbrium
nhat41 <- expression(-(K1-a12*K2)/(-1+a21*a12))
nhat42 <- expression(-(K2-a21*K1)/(-1+a21*a12))

#The derivatives from the Jacobian
j11 <- expression(-r1*(-K1+2*n1+a12*n2)/K1)
j12 <- expression(-r1*n1*a12/K1)
j21 <- expression(-r2*n2*a21/K2)
j22 <- expression(-r2*(-K2+2*n2+a21*n1)/K2)


#The values to start with
r1=1; r2=1
K1=1000; K2=1000
a12=0.5; a21=0.5

#Solve for equilibrium
n1 <- eval(nhat41)
n2 <- eval(nhat42)

#Construct the jacobian matrix
jac <- matrix(c(eval(j11),eval(j12),eval(j21),eval(j22)),nrow=2,byrow=T)

lambda <- eigen(jac)$values

#Second set of values
a12=1.5; a21=1.5

##Competitive oscillation

#install.packages("plot3D")
library(plot3D)
## Warning: package 'plot3D' was built under R version 4.0.3
LVcomp3 <- function (t, n, parms){
  r1 <- parms["r1"]; r2 <- parms["r2"]; r3 <- parms["r3"]
  K1 <- parms["K1"]; K2 <- parms["K2"]; K3 <- parms["K3"]
  a12 <- parms["a12"]; a21 <- parms["a21"]; a13 <- parms["a13"]; a23 <- parms["a23"]; a31 <- parms["a31"]; a32 <- parms["a32"]
  with(as.list(parms), {
    dn1 <- r1 * n[1] * (K1 - n[1] - a12 * n[2] - a13 * n[3])/K1
    dn2 <- r2 * n[2] * (K2 - n[2] - a21 * n[1] - a23 * n[3])/K2
    dn3 <- r3 * n[3] * (K3 - n[3] - a31 * n[1] - a32 * n[2])/K3
    list(c(dn1, dn2, dn3))
  })
}
#stable equilibrium
K <- c(K1=1, K2=9/19, K3=4/19)
alphas <- c(a12=2,a13=4,a21=1/3,a23=2,a31=1/3,a32=1/3)
r <- c(r1=6.255,r2=1,r3=6.255)
initialN <- c(1/19,3/19,1/36)
out.stable <- ode(y = initialN, times = 0:1000, func = LVcomp3, parms=c(K,alphas,r),method="ode45")
lines3D(out.stable[,2],out.stable[,3],out.stable[,4],phi=0,theta=310,colkey=FALSE)

#oscillation
r <- c(r1=6.655,r2=1,r3=6.655)
initialN <- c(1/19,3/19,1/36)
out.limit <- ode(y = initialN, times = 0:1000, func = LVcomp3, parms=c(K,alphas,r),method="ode45")
lines3D(out.limit[,2],out.limit[,3],out.limit[,4],phi=0,theta=310,colkey=FALSE)

##Resource competition

rcomp2 <- function(t,y,parms){
  with(as.list(parms), {
    ydot1 <- y[1]*(u1*y[3]-d1)
    ydot2 <- y[2]*(u2*y[3]-d2)
    ydot3 <- S-a*y[3]-w1*u1*y[1]*y[3]-w2*u2*y[2]*y[3]
    list(c(ydot1,ydot2,ydot3))
  })
}
u1 <- 0.1; u2 <- 0.05
d1 <- 0.1; d2 <- 0.1
w1 <- 0.1; w2 <- 0.1
S <- 10; a <- 0.5
initial<-c(1,1,1)
out.rcomp <- ode(y = initial, times = seq(1,100,by=0.1), func = rcomp2,
                 parms=c(u1=u1,u2=u2,d1=d1,d2=d2,w1=w1,w2=w2,S=S,a=a))
lines3D(out.rcomp[,2],out.rcomp[,3],out.rcomp[,4],phi=20,theta=300,colkey=FALSE,col="green",
        ticktype="detailed",lwd=2,xlim=c(0,1000),ylim=c(0,20),zlim=c(0,15))
